raw_data.title: Director
raw_data.description: Member of senior management and a technical expert in the company’s core service offerings, with experience leading and managing large projects funded by the US Government and other clients in the field of international development. S/he is responsible for providing strategic leadership and guidance and for managing teams. Director manages multiple projects of high complexity, often in overseas locations; mentors’ staff; and liaises closely with clients on all strategic issues. S/he is also responsible for designing, implementing, and managing business operations and process improvements.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert
raw_data.description: Experience and expertise in strategic and program management, assessments, monitoring and evaluation, methodology development, facilitation, training, report writing, business management, and/or organizational development. Serves as company’s representative on client projects, including on overseas assignments, and has extensive experience in company’s core service offerings. Responsible for planning, delivering, and managing activities on client projects and for liaising with the client. Develops company-wide technical services and products, including new methodologies for service and product delivery. Adept at using analytical tools and methodologies and is an expert in identifying key stakeholders, reviewing the effectiveness of existing programs, recommending programmatic strategies, and developing key performance indicators.

raw_data.title: Manager III
raw_data.description: Extensive project management and supervisory experience. Works in both specific and general subject areas and leads initiatives in these areas. Possesses a demonstrated ability to provide guidance and direction at the program and project level and to manage large, complex projects, including those implemented overseas. A critical  member of the team, a leader in most tasks, and works in a supervisory role with all project staff. Possesses technical expertise in one or more of company’s core services.

raw_data.title: Manager II
raw_data.description: Possesses project management and supervisory experience. Works in both specific and general subject areas. Demonstrated ability to provide guidance and direction at the program and project level and to manage projects, including those implemented overseas. A critical member of the team and works closely with all project staff. Demonstrates knowledge in one or more of company’s core services. Responsible for overseeing daily tasks to achieve project goals.

raw_data.title: Manager I
raw_data.description: Posseses project management experience. Works in both specific and general subject areas and possesses a demonstrated ability to complete assigned tasks. A critical member of the team and works closely with all project staff.

raw_data.title: Training Consultant III
raw_data.description: High-level expertise in designing and conducting complex training needs assessments and in developing and implementing courses and learning and professional development activities for clients. Manages the development of long-term learning strategies and leads and manages teams in the design and implementation of learning activities. Strengthens learning management and learning processes, develops tools and guidance to support knowledge management capacity, and keeps abreast of knowledge management and organizational learning best practices. Provides expert assistance in functional or technical area of expertise. Manages programs, activities, and staff.

raw_data.title: Training Consultant II
raw_data.description: designs and conducts complex training needs assessments and develops and implements courses and a range of learning and professional development activities for clients. Develops long-term learning strategies and works with teams in the design and implementation of learning activities. Strengthens learning management and learning processes, develops tools and guidance to support knowledge management capacity, keeps abreast of knowledge management and organizational learning best practices, and provides expert assistance in functional or technical area of expertise. Assists Training Consultant III.

raw_data.title: Training Consultant I
raw_data.description: Designs and conducts simple training needs assessments and delivers courses for clients. Supports the development of long-term learning strategies and supports teams in the design and implementation of learning activities. Helps develop tools and guidance to support knowledge management capacity, keeps abreast of knowledge management and organizational learning best practices, and provides assistance in functional or technical area of expertise. Assists Training Consultant II.
